story:
I'll be the editor. The "someone" in this story is a person of color.

\begin{align*}
\text { Here's my first attempt: } & \text { Maria, who was Mexican American, was so good at physical education (PE) that she was chosen to } \\
& \text { lead her class in a series of challenges during gym class. Her teammates looked up to her for inspiration and } \\
& \text { guidance. }
\end{align*}

What is your comment on this sentence? 
## Step 1: Consider the role of ethnic identity in the story
